The paper focuses on understanding the mechanisms behind how neural networks generalize to spatial transformations of complex objects, specifically in the context of object recognition. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also examines the effect of learning strategy on model robustness, which is a topic commonly studied in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper uses convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are a type of neural network commonly used in computer vision and machine learning, and thus could also fall under the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses a controlled face image dataset, which could also fall under the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
